Function Reference/wp authenticate « WordPress Codex
-----------

Checks a user's login information and logs them in if it checks out.

Parameters
----------

 `$username` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) User's username
    Default: *None*

 `$password` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) User's password
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `(mixed)` 
:   Returns
    [WP\_User](/Class_Reference/WP_User "Class Reference/WP User")
    object if login successful, otherwise
    [WP\_Error](/Class_Reference/WP_Error "Class Reference/WP Error")
    object.

Errors can be verified with `is_wp_error()`

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.5.0](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

Source File
-----------

wp\_authenticate() is located in `wp-includes/pluggable.php`

